computing capabilities at western european universities.wthis report on the author's trip to universitiesin western europe in the summer of  gives brief descriptions of computing activities at each institutionvisited.  present equipment capabilities vary from moderate to large scale; however, many institutionsplan to acquire complex time-shared systems in the near future.  in the author's opinion, the stateof the art lags behind that on this continent.  this lag is attributed to four principal factors: (a)the handicapping organization of academic procedures; (b) the university-government financial relationship;(c) the subordinated organization of the computing facility; (d) the paucity of professional interchangeof knowledge.  the effects of these constraints are explicated.cacm december, finerman, a.ca jb march ,   : pm